[ProMED-mail thanks Dr Acosta for this thorough review of the available background information. The point that increasing population movement into rural areas may change the habitat and increase the risk of human exposure is well taken. In this context, more information is needed on the habits of the species of Reduviidae insects found in the United States.

The seroprevalence surveys should be interpreted with caution. Serological assays perform differently in screening situations compared to a diagnostic situation, and a large proportion of the "positive" results could be false positives, thus the prevalence would be expected to be lower than the 2-4 percent cited from reference 6. - Mod.EP

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1mfK.]
